  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Each block contains the merkle-root of the MPT that contains all receipts. Receipts are serialised as a tuple of four values, and I want to understand how is the first value determined. \r\n\r\n- [Serialisation of the receipt](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/core/types/receipt.go#L342)\r\n- The first value correspond with [statusEncoding](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/core/types/receipt.go#L215-L223).\r\n\r\nI noticed that it can be either a \"boolean\" (`0x00` or `0x01`), or instead the merkle root of the state after applying the relevant tx. \r\n\r\nWhen is the boolean value used, and when is the merkle root used?\r\n\r\nFor more information about this, I opened a question in [Ethereum SE](https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/97266/building-receipts-proofs-using-only-information-from-rpc), and this issue: https://github.com/near/rainbow-bridge/issues/557",
